    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002521"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Shape resembling a funnel, narrow at the base and widening at the top</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'funnel shaped' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'shape'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002521.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Tapering">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Tapered"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">schmaler werdend</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">tapering</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002327"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Tapered quality characterized by continuous reduction in size towards a point</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'tapering' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'tapered'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002327.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/ParallelSided">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Shape"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">parallel seitig</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">parallel sided</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002485"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Shape quality having two sides that maintain a consistent distance relative to each other</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'parallel sided' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'shape'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002485.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Decussate">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/RegularSpatialPattern"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">decussate</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">gegenständig</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001953"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Spatial pattern involving opposite crossing elements in pairs, arranged diagonally</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'decussate' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'regular spatial pattern'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001953.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/ObservationProcess">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="Nd8a3b2d3b87c4dd582a295aba650e1e6"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="N1fac2ecf83714a36ac4ea826a0524c95"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">observation process</rdfs:label>
    <skos:example>The perception of the attribute yellow of a flower at daylight</skos:example>
    <iof-av:counterExample>a process of a human determining the length of an object with a caliper</iof-av:counterExample>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Process for determining attributes like dependent continuants, temporal regions, or process characteristics of entities as perceived by humans, which are of interest and categorical</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicDefinition xml:lang="en">ObservationProcess(x) ↔ ∃b ((Agent(b) ∧ ∃c (ObservationCapability(c) ∧ hasCapability(b, c))) ∧ obo:BFO_0000057(x, b)) ∧ ∃d (MorphologicalQuality(d) ∧ hasSpecifiedOutput(x, d))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">every instance of 'observation process' is defined as exactly that 'obo:BFO_0000057' some an instance of 'Agent' and that 'hasCapability' some 'observation capability' and that 'hasSpecifiedOutput' some 'Morphological quality'</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Pigmented">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/DegreeOfPigmentation"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pigmented</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002248"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Pigmented is a degree of pigmentation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of having substances produced by living organisms that have a color resulting from selective color absorption</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'pigmented' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'degree of pigmentation'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002248.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Netted">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/IrregularSpatialPattern"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">netted</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">vernetzt</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001947"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Irregular spatial pattern featuring a mesh-like network or arrangement</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'netted' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'irregular spatial pattern'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001947.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/LanceolateTriangular">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Lanceolate"/>
