    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Concave 3-D shape characterized by an inversely clavate form</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'obclavate' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'concave 3-d shape'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002213.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
