    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Concave 3D shape resembling a boat or ship structure, typically elongated and hollowed</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'navicular' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'concave 3-d shape'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000344.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/MaterialStructure">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/MorphologicalQuality"/>
    <obo:IAO_0000119 xml:lang="en">“Material - Classification by structure.” Wikipedia The Free Encyclopedia, https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Material#Classification_by_structure. Accessed 13 Jan. 2023.</obo:IAO_0000119>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/co"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Materialstruktur</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">material structure</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Structure quality of materials on diffent dimentional scales, ranging from macro, meso, micro to nano scale</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'material structure' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'Morphological quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Lobed">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Lobate"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">gelappt</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">lobed</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001979"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Lobate characteristic marked by distinct sections or lobes</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'lobed' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'lobate'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001979.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/PaleBlack">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Black"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">blass schwarz</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pale black</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002004"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Black color with reduced intensity or saturation</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'pale black' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'black'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002004.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/DesaturatedRed">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Red"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">desaturated red</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">entsättigtes Rot</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001284"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Color hue characterized by red tones mixed with white or grey, reducing saturation</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'desaturated red' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'red'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001284.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Tapered">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Shape"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Sharp"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">spitz zulaufend</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">tapered</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001500"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Shape narrowing or gradually reducing in thickness towards one end</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'tapered' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'shape'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001500.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/DesaturatedCyan">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Cyan"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">desaturated cyan</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">entsättigtes Cyan</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001270"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Color hue where cyan tones are mixed with white or grey, reducing saturation</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'desaturated cyan' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'cyan'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001270.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/YShaped">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Shape2D"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">y förmig</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">y shaped</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001201"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Y-shaped is a concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of resembling the form of the letter Y</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'y shaped' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'shape2 d'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001201.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/NonFragile">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Fragility"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">nicht zerbrechlich</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">non fragile</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001716"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Non-fragile is a structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of being able to withstand great strain without tearing or breaking</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'non fragile' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'fragility'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001716.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Parallelodromous">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Branched"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Parallelodrom</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">parallelodromous</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001968"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Quality having two or more parallel primary branches originating beside each other and converging apically</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'parallelodromous' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'branched'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001968.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Colored">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Color"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">colored</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">farbig</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000336"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Color quality exhibiting visible hues</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'colored' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'color'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000336.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Pink">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Color"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Red"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pink</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000954"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Color hue produced by blending red with white, often appearing as soft or pale red</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'pink' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'color'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000954.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Hydrocephalic">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Edematous"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hydrocephalic</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">wasserkopfartig</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001853"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Edematous quality presenting swollen head due to fluid accumulation</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'hydrocephalic' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'edematous'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001853.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Wavy">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Curvature"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">wavy</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">wellig</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000211"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Curvature marked by repetitive undulations or waves</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'wavy' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'curvature'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000211.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Yellow">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Color"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">gelb</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">yellow</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000324"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Color hue perceptible between green and orange due to wavelengths around 570-590 nanometers</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'yellow' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'color'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000324.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Organized">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/OrganizationQuality"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">organisiert</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">organized</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000938"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Organized is a structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of exhibiting organization</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'organized' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'organization quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000938.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/MultiLocalised">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/SpatialPattern"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">mehrfachlokalisiert</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">multi localised</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001791"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Multi-localised is a spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of being confined or restricted to multiple locations</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'multi localised' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'spatial pattern'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001791.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="N8f5052841bf4431d9d0c9ac85882f126">
