    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Shape displaying a curved or spiral form, often with overlapping edges</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'curled' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'shape'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000405.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Solid">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/MorphologicalComposition"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">fest</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">solid</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001535"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Composition observation exhibiting robust and firm structure, lacking voids or significant liquid content</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'solid' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'Morphological composition'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001535.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/CorymbLike">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Shape"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">corymb like</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">doldenförmig</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002455"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Shape resembling a corymb structure where flower stalks grow upward, forming a flat or slightly convex surface</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'corymb like' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'shape'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002455.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Stretched">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Elongated"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">gestreckt</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">stretched</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Stretched is a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of being elongated or extended without breaking, increasing its length or area</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'stretched' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'elongated'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Disheveled">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/IrregularSpatialPattern"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">disheveled</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">durcheinander</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001605"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Irregular spatial pattern involving untidy or disordered arrangement</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'disheveled' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'irregular spatial pattern'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001605.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/ScaleneTriangular">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Triangular"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">scalene triangular</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">ungleichseitig dreieckig</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002308"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Scalene triangular is a triangular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of having all sides of unequal length</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'scalene triangular' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'triangular'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002308.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Spotty">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/MultiColored"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">fleckig</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">spotty</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002261"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Multi-colored pattern characterized by distinct spots or patches</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'spotty' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'multi colored'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002261.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/FiberShaped">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Subcylindrical"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">faserförmig</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">fiber shaped</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002309"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Subcylindrical shape resembling a fiber or strand, typically long and thin</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'fiber shaped' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'subcylindrical'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002309.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Waxiness">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/MorphologicalComposition"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">wachsigkeit</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">waxiness</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002381"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Waxiness is a composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the presence of long-chain aliphatic lipids on the surface of an organism</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'waxiness' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'Morphological composition'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002381.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Conical">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Convex3DShape"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">conical</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">kegelförmig</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002021"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">3D shape resembling a cone, with a circular base tapering smoothly to a point</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'conical' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'convex 3-d shape'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002021.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/PinLike">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Shape"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">nadelförmig</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pin like</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002458"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Pin-like is a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of being thin and lacking outgrowths</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'pin like' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'shape'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002458.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/DesaturatedOrange">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Orange"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">desaturated orange</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">entsättigtes Orange</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001278"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Color hue mixing orange tones with white or grey to reduce brightness</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'desaturated orange' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'orange'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001278.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Unstructured">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Structure"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">unstructured</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">unstrukturiert</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001412"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Unstructured is a structural quality inhering in a bearer due to lacking distinct structure</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'unstructured' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'structure'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001412.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/DeepPink">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Pink"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">deep pink</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">dunkelrosa</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001258"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Color hue manifesting dark and intense pink tones</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'deep pink' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'pink'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001258.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/PlugShaped">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Shape"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">plug shaped</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0040012"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Plug shaped is a shape quality in the form of a plug, being tube-like and expanded on one end</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'plug shaped' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'shape'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0040012.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Turgor">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Structure"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">turgor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">turgor</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001620"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Turgor is a structural quality inhering in a cell or blood vessel or capillary due to being in a rigid state of fullness resulting from pressure of the contents against the wall or membrane</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'turgor' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'structure'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001620.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/PearShaped">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Convex3DShape"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">birnenförmig</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pear shaped</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0005002"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Pear shaped is a convex 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of having a shape that tapers near the top and bulges toward the base</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'pear shaped' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'convex 3-d shape'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0005002.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Damage">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Structure"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Schaden</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">damage</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001020"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Structural quality indicating harm or impairment to an entity</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'damage' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'structure'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001020.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Lobate">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/SurfaceFeatureShape"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">gelappt</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">lobate</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001367"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Surface feature shape delineated by rounded projections or lobes</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'lobate' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'surface feature shape'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001367.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Collapsed">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Structure"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">collapsed</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">eingefallen</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001478"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Structure characterized by a reduction in volume or internal void space</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'collapsed' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'structure'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001478.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Fragile">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Fragility"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">fragile</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">zerbrechlich</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001362"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">Fragility quality indicating susceptibility to breaking or damage under stress</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'fragile' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'fragility'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001362.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
